docker file ----------------- docker image ----------------conatiner
              docker build                   docker run

COMPONENTS: 

       FROM: used to define base image
       COPY: used to copy data from HOST(server) to CONTAINER
       ADD:  used to copy data from HOST to CONTAINER and it will download the files from internet and send those files to container
       RUN:  used to execute commands while creating an image (RUN is used to setup everything in inmage)
                     eg: RUN apt install git -y 

       CMD:  used to execute commands while creating a container. We can execute a single CMD in a docker file. (start applications)
                     eg: CMD npm start
                         CMD python app.py
       ENTRYPOINT: defines the main command that will always run when a container starts.
       EXPOSE:   used to publish port num
       ARG:      is used to define variables for which we can't access in container (only for building image)
       ENV:      used to define variables which can be accessed in container
       WORKDIR:  used to set default path on a conrtainer
       MAINTAINER: used to add author details of docker file
       LABEL : used to add description about image

       
